â€œWhat color is your functionâ€ is a problem explored in this article. In languages which have Async baked in via special keywords (e.g JavaScript async/await) it becomes a pain to refactor and to combine synchronous and asynchronous code. If you make one function deep in the call stack async, all the callers will have to be made Async as well, or await() the results. With effects you donâ€™t have this issue as there are no keywords and no special behavior. Async is simply done with effect handlers. â†©
